  "text": "Robert Allen et al. described a series of 27 Pap flaps for breast reconstruction, all them were successful with minimal complications and minimal fat necrosis. [CITATION_1] In some situations, a large volumen of tissue is needed to achieve a good cosmesis and symmetry with the contralateral breast, combined flaps 5 or performing two \"stacked flaps\" to be reliable and feasible choices.",
